\ with-stream: run a body over an already-open stream and close it however the
\ body exits. Uses start-process, so this test is skipped under WASI (no
\ fork/exec) via wasm-skip.txt. Batch mode: every line's exact stdout is golden.

\ ---- normal: read a child's stdout through the guard; stream closed after ----
[ "printf" "hello" ] start-process :out @ [: read :] with-stream . cr           \ hello

\ ---- throw mid-body still closes the stream; the exception propagates ----
[: [ "printf" "x" ] start-process :out @ [: drop "streamboom" throw :] with-stream :]
  [: "stream-caught " . . :] try-catch cr
